2 Model: \(H_2: \delta < 0\)

# Read data Dr. Smith
Winter <- c(-0.05,0.41,0.17,-0.13,0.00,-0.05,0.00,0.17,0.29,0.04,0.21,0.08,0.37,0.17,0.08,-0.04,-0.04,0.04,-0.13,-0.12,0.04,0.21,0.17,
       0.17,0.17,0.33,0.04,0.04,0.04,0.00,0.21,0.13,0.25,-0.05,0.29,0.42,-0.05,0.12,0.04,0.25,0.12)
 
Summer <- c(0.00,0.38,-0.12,0.12,0.25,0.12,0.13,0.37,0.00,0.50,0.00,0.00,-0.13,-0.37,-0.25,-0.12,0.50,0.25,0.13,0.25,0.25,0.38,0.25,0.12,
      0.00,0.00,0.00,0.00,0.25,0.13,-0.25,-0.38,-0.13,-0.25,0.00,0.00,-0.12,0.25,0.00,0.50,0.00)

x <- Winter-Summer # allowed because it is a within-subjects design
x <- x/sd(x)       # standardize

ndata <- length(Winter) # number of subjects

data  <- list("x", "ndata") # to be passed on to JAGS

myinits <- list(
  list(delta = -abs(rnorm(1,0,1)), deltaprior = -abs(rnorm(1,0,1)), sigmatmp = .1),
  list(delta = -abs(rnorm(1,0,1)), deltaprior = -abs(rnorm(1,0,1)), sigmatmp = .2),
  list(delta = -abs(rnorm(1,0,1)), deltaprior = -abs(rnorm(1,0,1)), sigmatmp = .3))

# Parameters to be monitored
# 교재에는 deltaprior를 표집했지만, 관찰하지 않았다.
parameters <- c("delta", "deltaprior")

model_text <- "
# One-Sample Order Restricted Comparison of Means
model{
  # Data
  for (i in 1:ndata){
    x[i] ~ dnorm(mu,lambda)
  } 
  mu <- delta*sigma
  lambda <- pow(sigma,-2)
  
  # delta and sigma Come From (Half) Cauchy Distributions
  lambdadelta ~ dchisqr(1)
  delta ~ dnorm(0,lambdadelta)T(,0)
  lambdasigma ~ dchisqr(1)
  sigmatmp ~ dnorm(0,lambdasigma)
  sigma <- abs(sigmatmp)
  
  # Sampling from Prior Distribution for Delta
  deltaprior ~ dnorm(0,lambdadeltaprior)T(,0)
  lambdadeltaprior ~ dchisqr(1)
}
"

samples <- jags(data, inits=myinits, parameters,
                 model.file = textConnection(model_text),
                 n.chains=3, n.iter=10000,
         n.burnin=1000, n.thin=1, DIC=T)

# Collect posterior samples across all chains:
delta.posterior <- samples$BUGSoutput$sims.list$delta

Censored 자료이므로 logspline으로 확률밀도를 계산할 때 주의가 필요하다. 첫째, posterior의 영점밀도를 계산할 때 ubound=0를 넣어야 한다. 둘째, MCMC 표본을 활용하지 않고 prior의 영점밀도를 계산하려면 분포가 좌우 대칭이므로 두 배 곱해준다.

#============ BFs based on logspline fit ===========================
library(polspline) # this package can be installed from within R
fit.posterior <- logspline(delta.posterior) # 경고 나온다. 아래처럼 'ubound=0'을 넣어야 한다.
Warning in logspline(delta.posterior): Not all models could be fitted
# plot(fit.posterior) 플롯으로 그려보면, 아래 'ubound=0'을 넣은 경우와 차이는 없다.

#============ BFs based on logspline fit ===========================
fit.posterior <- logspline(delta.posterior, ubound=0) # censored 자료라서 'ubound=0' 넣어야 한다.

# # 95% confidence interval:
# x0 <- qlogspline(0.025,fit.posterior)
# x1 <- qlogspline(0.975,fit.posterior)

posterior <- dlogspline(0, fit.posterior) # this gives the pdf at point delta = 0
prior     <- 2*dcauchy(0) # 두 배 해준다. height of order--restricted prior at delta = 0
BF01      <- posterior/prior
BF01
[1] 13.75462

대립가설 \(H_2: \delta < 0\)보다 영가설 \(H_0: \delta = 0\)이 약 14배 더 증거에 부합한다.

대립가설 \(H_3: \delta > 0\)보다 영가설 \(H_0: \delta = 0\)이 약 4배 더 증거에 부합한다. 결과적으로, \(H_1\)(지난 단락)은 \(H_2\)보다 낫지만 \(H_3\)보다 못하다.
